pub.citation: Tokuoka, T. 2007. Molecular phylogenetic analysis of Euphorbiaceae sensu stricto based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences and ovule and seed character evolution. Journal of Plant Research 120: 511-522.

pmmd.notes: Single most parsimonious tree resulting from the combined analyses of rbcL, atpB, matK and 18S rDNA sequence data (tree length = 5638, consistency index = 0.472, retention index = 0.647). The numbers above the branches represent bootstrap percentages (?0%). Abbreviation for each clade followed Wurdack et al. (2005)
